name: Mass Change Queries
description:
You are given an array a consisting of n integers. You have to process q
queries to this array; each query is given as four numbers l, r, x and y,
denoting that for every i such that l ≤ i ≤ r and ai = x you have to set ai
equal to y. Print the array after all queries are processed. Input The first
line contains one integer n (1 ≤ n ≤ 200000) — the size of array a. The second
line contains n integers a1, a2, ..., an (1 ≤ ai ≤ 100) — the elements of
array a. The third line contains one integer q (1 ≤ q ≤ 200000) — the number
of queries you have to process. Then q lines follow. i-th line contains four
integers l, r, x and y denoting i-th query (1 ≤ l ≤ r ≤ n, 1 ≤ x, y ≤ 100).
Output Print n integers — elements of array a after all changes are made.
Example Input 5 1 2 3 4 5 3 3 5 3 5 1 5 5 1 1 5 1 5 Output 5 2 5 4 5
